[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering coverage maps**\n\nI’m pondering whether native agent coverage maps only test with direct usage. It seems like this could limit the scope of what we learn from those tests. I wonder if they’re capturing enough real-world scenarios or if they’re missing out on potential issues. It's something worth thinking about more, as I really want to ensure that these maps are providing valuable insights for users. Let's explore this further.\n\n**Considering Java list methods**\n\nI’m thinking about how commonly `java/util/LinkedList` and `java/util/ArrayList` are used in reverse. They return an `AbstractList`, which is interesting. I also need to figure out if the `classWriter` should use `COMPUTE_FRAMES` only and not `COMPUTE_MAXS`, but the docs say it implies both. Maybe it’s safer to use `COMPUTE_FRAMES | COMPUTE_MAXS` just in case? I want to stay dynamic in my approach while figuring this out!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0237394f573391680169fb8e0e6bf881a0b0dabfff57628dc3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-44jUwyu7yBpuOclad0VwgoiFWjOJvJL6YZhj4uUV5pNqvlb939lvSxdLQ-tlq-l6L8yy5La7IK-6-SWz1w-yMgrQGRfZ1sYNUFd5mDPoNN6KxmNfrNdbz_fagzfAQTtTMYqe17FwCy_BeUKnNkmTshyV7n9rn9zJkRYUz7mm4kfnp1A4mjzlCW-ZQ5S1KMkZfza0yTB8d9a7eKAUz1vSpOwVNrRmcF9GKQ7GoeYnaiN125zvzwHPtkmxu5iHX3B1ujHi00yLti7LpP4VZJwQvVGDaffAMHg9WUPDndZw94LtBoxCaM7FfYkjJ_86sW_YAMk4qz0qJOdNpe9_nST-or1Op0a6fhUTOuUYHc404X2ZGXbLqRmZbSjb35W2Mk_JeD49S-On1mlPhR13Cf5wGg7BUqxYqp0oZSWOC8PpWZpBaWze_vhZgFr0i_6Hcpj3W4Up6SS1ws63TenQAHUT712GT4hvAVp02eK00pSZUo179tSYMn4VnX2tysSQi8LYmfHTb-tyZv4v2Szc8HrzNypm-Ff_HI0GZ4Jc_wBAxhtKM2_xbVK0nlaLMkPVH4BNKcyuc8AeEx_ugKYep_z0v1BTZ1HpxAdZQ4l9OBGwZ3Phy-j-mSpaQrs4rwEoWCmEiO3EPmpqKzsx43hjc7SY2GfAFRG4wJOuyoactHAA1DavGIIAJXIxDQ_ctNDH5npZcezFiCMw1VhKJ9W3rjQas4ft-RxWoewL5bcV7OJbg3E0o0EUQC8eaAsmNpwb8fOTajQ7DyI84rUfKzw5Plt37yi6PE9uQZe93FEQRxE4pJTt86iNBp43CJ_KCRFsTnasQ